guideing failed.  Kelraz and crew called the raid due to lack of chanters but there was a large number of people there that still wanted to have a go.  We ended up with 2 chanters and almost got her, one more and she would have dropped.  Another thing that should be thought of, and I have, is paladins.  The more the better.  Stuns will not stop her from melee but they will stop her from casting CH.  The incentive, pali epic drops.  Normally, Vox will drop 2 scales and 2 books, so there should be 4 happy people there.  For naggy, having LoH available for agro and cleric recovery would be very nice, especially if it we say 1 per group. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bardsrule1169>BardsRule1169</A> at: 12/12/01 6:58:53 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ualthor64.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Althor64</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/12/01 8:02:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=315.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid 15 or 16 DEC</span><hr size=1> I will likely attend<br>
